The paper deals with index coding, which is a problem in information theory and communication networks. The use of graph theory and combinatorics in the approach suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are likely categories. The use of linear codes suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a likely category. The paper also deals with optimization, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible categories.
